{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πάχν-η</b>, ἡ, <br /> (πήγνυμι) <b>hoar-frost, rime</b> (defined as frozen rain, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-1st c.BC: Posidonius Historicus cited in 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 7.153), 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.476; π. ἑῴα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 25; τὸ ἐπὶ γῆς συμπαγὲν ἐκ δρόσου γενόμενον π. λέγεται 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 59e \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to κρύσταλλος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Theognetus Comicus 1.3: _plural_, πάχναι καὶ χάλαζαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 188b; ἀπέκαυσεν ἡ π. τὰς ἀμπέλους 4th-3rd c.BC: Philippides Comicus 25.4. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, γήρως εὐρῶτα καὶ πάχνην the mould and <b>frost</b> of age, descriptive of an old man's grey hair, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Comica Adespota” 650a\">Refs</a>], compare 381; π. κουροβόρος <b>clotted blood</b> of the eaten children, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1512 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8672","accentedUnicode":"πάχνη","shortDef":"frost","mediumDef":"frost","stepGloss":"frost","stepTransliteration":"pachnē","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}